node.text:
After the the struggles of the @usabmx GA nationals 
Kids asked to start “training”
Fun for me to be able to pass on a few decades of trial and error. The complaining brings back fun memories, I’ve never seen any individual at the highest levels of sport not complain 😂
It’s truly part of learning to suffer through it, the ones who are quiet seem to be the ones that just quit in my experience 🤷🏽‍♂️
I love their grind and never wanting to quit attitude 
Dads finally getting to give when asked and needed 🙌🏻😍

node.text: I am really proud to be part of Moto40 with these guys. We all bring something different to the table and I’m really excited for the partnership. With the official Grand opening this weekend I hope everyone can start coming out to ride and enjoy what we have created here. We came together with a common goal- Making a place all ages and levels can have fun riding! Load up the bikes - let’s go 🤙🏽

node.text:
Crazy to think for the first time in 20 years I won’t be lining up at the first @supercrosslive race. 
BUT I’m excited @cbdmd.usa asked me to do some weekly “HOT TAKES” 
Make sure you’re following them and let us know what you want to hear from us.. 
2️⃣2️⃣👊🏽

node.text:
Man 2009 was a fun year!
After SX I went back to Australia for some time off as I only had a SX only contract 
Got bored and missed my badass team and bike so decided to race MX after two years off😅😤
It was a grind to get back up to speed, but I was excited to find a feeling outdoors that I’d always been chasing . 
09 was so good. learned so much, wish it lasted into 2010 and beyond. 
The great outdoors is now streaming for the first time ever @tgomotocross check it out! 
@mrstwotwo @thereal_goose @slasher200

node.text:
Today was one for the books! 😂
Stories that’ll bring some laughs for years to come,I had a blast with the boys going trail riding.
I grew up having access to the bush 🇦🇺 (woods) 🇺🇸 and spent hours riding and getting lost -it’s always half the fun. 
In all my crazy shenanigans over the years I’ve never ran out of options where I had to cross a river 😂 ✅ 
Very limited options today 
We tried climbing back out but it was 400 meters straight up and impossible to make it out
@kr_557 made the call that we weren’t going to be able to make it back up!
Side note it was his choice of trail that got us stuck in the first place but I somehow still trusted him 😅 
So back to the bottom it was 🤷🏽‍♂️
This video makes me laugh so hard -man I love motorcycles !
Luckily Ive been watching running wild with @beargrylls 🤙🏾 
What a day boys. 
@justinp_21_  @sheetmetal220 @layne523 @gatlin_welborn17 @mountainmotorsports_

node.text:
Since aging up and classing up @twotwotatereed has had a really tough time, we’ve yelled at each other more times than not, the roller coaster has been a real! But LIL man never stopped digging! 
As most parents can relate, after a 14+ hour drive home, long up and down three days of racing 
The last thing you want to do is jump outta the car and straight to dropping gates 🤦🏽‍♂️😅
But I love his willingness to TRY
Here we are next race and he made the main and fought up to 3rd in his main. Really proud of you kiddo! ❤️👏🏼

node.text:
My baby girl is 9 today
Crazy to think how scared I was to have a girl! And funny now that it’s one of my most favorite things about being a Dad. 
She is a fire cracker and takes zero shit, yet plays daddies girl most of the time ❤️
Seems momma bear is automatically harder on her than the boys. so it helps keep her on team dad haha 
Of all 3 kids; Kiah will ask questions about everything that I’m doing to her bikes. Wants to help and/or learn, I love that she is never scared to do anything, the bravest of them all! Her love for all things wheels makes me so proud. 
Anything you put your mind to “SIS” you got my full support 
Get em @twotwokiahreed ❤️😘

node.text:
I will call him mini me. 
I purposely tried to steer him away from Moto. Not because I don’t love it. I LOVE IT. That didn’t mean he had to. He grew up immersed into the scene but he never had that die hard obsession for it. So I didn’t push it at all. Racing moto requires unwavering passion and that isn’t taught! Skills come but desire is what fuels you when the days are tough. Only the tough survive or succeed in this sport. As soon as I retired he started racing BMX & now just wants to ride. It’s cool to watch his own desires and passions come forward. I’m just watching his story unfold and trying to help him realize his dreams in life whatever they will be. Wild Dad moment to watch him on the big track yesterday and following me over his first big jumps. @twotwotatereed

node.text:
After the the struggles of the @usabmx GA nationals 
Kids asked to start “training”
Fun for me to be able to pass on a few decades of trial and error. The complaining brings back fun memories, I’ve never seen any individual at the highest levels of sport not complain 😂
It’s truly part of learning to suffer through it, the ones who are quiet seem to be the ones that just quit in my experience 🤷🏽‍♂️
I love their grind and never wanting to quit attitude 
Dads finally getting to give when asked and needed 🙌🏻😍
